Share this on WhatsAppSpread the lovePresident Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated Gov. Dapo Abiodun of Ogun on the occasion of his 62nd birthday.
In a congratulatory message issued by his Spokesman, Malam Garba Shehu, on Monday in Abuja, the president joined family, friends and well-wishers in praying for God’s continued guidance, strength and wisdom for the governor.
He described Abiodun as ”a shining example of a leader who works round the clock to meet the expectations of his people”.
The president recognised the important contributions the governor of the Gateway State has made and continues to make in national development.
He expressed the hope that the celebration of another birth year in health and joy would continue to inspire the governor to do more for a better future for Ogun people and Nigerians.
